      "target": {
        "kind": "issue",
        "state": "open",
        "locked": false,
        "title": "Lag in merged icons mode when switching usage chart views",
        "body": "Thank you for providing the new build!\n\nHowever, I can still observe lag in certain scenarios.\n\n**Steps to reproduce:**\n\n1. Enable merged icons mode.\n2. Hover over a model.\n3. In the newly opened window containing the usage chart, switch between the two view options: Session and Weekly.\n4. After switching back and forth a few times, the lag starts to appear, usually around the third click.\n\n**Observed behavior:**\n\nThe UI becomes noticeably laggy when switching between the Session and Weekly usage chart views.\nThe lag can be temporarily resolved by clicking elsewhere, as long as the usage chart window does not appear again.\nOne subtle behavior I noticed is that before the window disappears, it seems to block keyboard input in other windows. This might be useful for debugging.\n\n**Additional note:**\n\nThe lag in the overview under merged icons mode still appears occasionally, but it has improved significantly in recent builds.\n\n**Environment:**\n\n* MacBook Pro 14-inch, 2021\n* Apple M1 Pro\n* 16 GB RAM\n* macOS 26.5.1 (25F80)\n* Codex 0.33.0 (80)",
